Both Melbourne and Sydney are fantastic destinations in Australia, each offering unique experiences. Since you love tennis, Melbourne might be the perfect choice for you! Melbourne is home to the famous Australian Open, one of the four Grand Slam tennis tournaments. If you visit during January, you can catch some world-class tennis action at Melbourne Park. In addition to tennis, Melbourne also boasts vibrant neighborhoods, renowned coffee culture, and impressive street art scene. Make sure to explore the laneways for hidden gems and delicious food options. If you're up for a day trip, you can also visit the beautiful Great Ocean Road from Melbourne. So, for a tennis lover like you, Melbourne offers the perfect blend of sports and culture!

If you prioritize comfort and service, airlines like Emirates, Qatar Airways, and Singapore Airlines are known for their excellent service and comfortable flights. These airlines often have layovers in their respective hub cities, such as Dubai, Doha, or Singapore. If you're looking for a more budget-friendly option, airlines like China Southern, Air China, or Cathay Pacific often offer competitive prices with layovers in cities like Guangzhou, Beijing, or Hong Kong.

When booking your flight, consider factors like layover duration, total travel time, and any additional costs for baggage or seat selection. One of the most popular and beautiful beaches in Melbourne is St. Kilda Beach. It's located just a short tram ride from the city center and offers a lively atmosphere with plenty of cafes, restaurants, and bars nearby. You can enjoy swimming, sunbathing, or even try windsurfing or kitesurfing if you're feeling adventurous. Another great beach is Brighton Beach, known for its iconic colorful bathing boxes lining the shore, making it a perfect spot for Instagram-worthy photos.
